Third-party attributions for libscuffedrdma middleware
=======================================================

This directory contains code adapted from the following third-party
projects. Each project's license is reproduced below.

---

autoscriptlabs/libmesh-rdma
---------------------------

Upstream: https://github.com/autoscriptlabs/libmesh-rdma
Files adapted from libmesh-rdma:
  - middleware/rdma_gid_discovery.py
    (ports mesh_rdma_find_ipv4_gid_index and helpers from
     src/mesh_rdma_core.c)
  - middleware/rdma_bootstrap.py
    (ports mesh_rdma_qp_info_t, mesh_rdma_send_handshake, and
     mesh_rdma_accept_handshake from src/mesh_rdma_core.c)
  - middleware/rdma_qp_state_machine.py
    (ports mesh_rdma_create_qp and mesh_rdma_connect_qp
     from src/mesh_rdma_core.c)

The adaptation is a Python rewrite against pyverbs rather than a
verbatim copy of the C source. The retry loop structure, the IPv4-mapped
GID detection heuristic, the binary 64-byte QpInfo wire format, and the
direct-GRH RTR transition are all derived from the libmesh-rdma design.

